DESCRIBE THE EVENT, TRY TO INCLUDE HOW I: The event is structured to focus on three specific coding problems from LeetCode, selected to cover a range of difficulty levels and topics such as algorithms and data structures. This is aimed at enhancing students' problem-solving and coding skills by introducing them to best practices and efficient approaches to coding challenges. The workshop will include a detailed walkthrough of each problem, emphasizing optimal solutions and strategies like time complexity reduction and space optimization. Participants will learn how to approach different types of problems, identify common patterns, and apply appropriate algorithms. Additionally, the workshop is intended for students interested in programming and those preparing for technical interviews, offering insights into how tech companies evaluate coding proficiency.

ORGANIZATION: Keyboard Club at UC San Diego
NAME OF EVENT: Studio Keebli: Keyboard Meet Of Your Dreams
VENUE: Price Center West - Ballroom AB + East Ballroom
DESCRIBE THE EVENT, TRY TO INCLUDE HOW I: This event is a high-scope event that is designed to introduce, foster, and facilitate a community at UC San Diego revolving around keyboards. With a planned 25 Artists & 25 Artisan Makers, Vendors, and Content Creators, we hope to create the most compelling and diverse experience in keyboards in the World. This event will likely be one of the World's biggest Keyboard Exhibitions - with a planned $15,000-$20,000 in product being given back directly to UC San Diego students to equitize the hobby.

This event is the first day of dress/tech rehearsals (2PM-6PM) for a performance in Spring Quarter in which Aequora Ballet Company members will dance classical and contemporary ballet choreography. The show will feature two other dance groups on campus, Muse Dance Company and Ikigai Dance Company.
The theme of the show is Alice in Wonderland interpretations. For company members, the event itself and preparation for it aim to improve studentsâ€™ out-of-classroom experience by providing students with a social event, while promoting a balance of academics, personal growth, and extracurriculars. For potential attendees, the performance is an opportunity for students and the UCSD community at large to gain exposure to the artsâ€“ballet specificallyâ€“and enrich their experience at UCSD with a live performance of ballet conveniently located on campus. Student attendees may also appreciate the opportunity of connecting with other peers who attend the performance, along with connecting with their dance-maker peers by witnessing their styles of storytelling through movement.  
Overall, Aequora Ballet Company aims to foster a diverse and inclusive classical and contemporary dance community for students to connect and improve their dancing, as well as the opportunity to perform in an annual showcase in which they can share their work with the UCSD community. This is our third year in-person as a student organization and fourth year overall, and we would use the funds to cover the Price Center venue and services.

DESCRIBE THE EVENT, TRY TO INCLUDE HOW I: We will hold a workshop on how you can use amateur radio to contact satellites such as the ISS. We will also go over telemetry data, how repeaters work and how EME communication works.

ORGANIZATION: Student Support Services Club (SSSC or SSS Club)
DESCRIBE THE EVENT, TRY TO INCLUDE HOW I: Our organization provides a supportive space for students to interact and connect with each other through school events, learning environments (classroom and tutoring workshops), and personal associations throughout the year. For this reason, the mission statement of our organization is to empower underrepresented students in pursuing higher education and to celebrate cultural diversity. Each year our event has several components to follow our mission statement. Firstly, the event will gather the students in our organization who are from different backgrounds and UCSD colleges to celebrate their accomplishments and growth during the academic year. The event will also validate the achievements of the students in our organization and empower them as we come together as a community and support each other. For instance, the graduating seniors and their families, along with current club members will be recognized and honored for their achievements. In addition, the event will celebrate the diversity in the organization by having food catering that showcases the different cultures in our organization. Throughout the event, we will have a keynote speaker and a senior speaker who will inspire our students to succeed in higher education.

Health Summit is an event that brings together professional and graduate student speakers to provide attendees with opportunities for professional development and networking. This Health conference is a space where attendees can interact with speakers and gain insight on their lives in different healthcare fields. As part of our mission, Health Summit Workshop day promotes education and awareness of health issues to productively direct attendees towards their future health professions. My Neighbor Totoro, a Studio Ghibli film, will serve as inspiration for our 2024, 10th annual Health Summit.
